Elastic Team OpenAI - Powered Text Generator Challenge

Date: 
June 23, 2023 5:00 PM - July 7, 2023 5:00 PM EAT
DropdownAdd to calendar
Zeamanual Feleke
Giovanni Caiazzo
Claud Watari
Abida Abro
+2

Overview 

Hello Elastic Team Members! Welcome to Elastic Team NodeJS Challenge - Real-Time Chat.

We are delighted to present this challenge that not only sharpens your programming skills but also gives you a taste of the challenges faced by developers in their daily work. Our aim is to expose you to real-world tasks and issues via the Elastic Team Challenges.

For this challenge, your goal is to create a polished, user-friendly web application that leverages OpenAI's API to generate text based on user prompts. The key here is to create a platform that is versatile. It should cater to casual users seeking fun and engaging text-generation experiences but also function as a powerful tool for professional writers, content creators, and individuals in creative fields.

We encourage you to showcase your creativity and problem-solving abilities while adhering to the best practices in NodeJS and web development. Emphasize scalability, efficiency, and seamless user experiences.

During the course of the challenge, feel free to use the Comments section to ask questions, discuss ideas, or seek clarification on any aspect of the task at hand. This is a collaborative community and we believe in learning and growing together.

Skills tested: NodeJS or Python
Difficulty: Medium - High

General:

  • Familiarize yourself with the OpenAI API: https://platform.openai.com/docs/introduction
  • You may use NodeJS or Python to build the application.
  • Feel free to use either GPT-4 or GPT-3.5 Models.
  • Follow the page layout and design elements based on the provided Figma layout. https://www.figma.com/file/ydEWb5yRqnt6DWl9sXBfy1/ET-Open-AI-Text-Generator?type=design&node-id=0%3A1&t=ArlkBaMKlZdhq2rJ-1
  • The application should be web-based and accessible via modern web browsers.
  • The application must integrate with OpenAI's API for text generation.

Text Generator Application Features:
1. Layout

  • Page layout should consist of 3 sections:
    • Header (fixed on top)
    • Main chat area (scrollable)
    • Input field (fixed at the bottom).
  • The header should contain the logo and title.
  • There should be distinct icons for AI and ET in the main chat area. Messages from AI should align left, while those from ET should align right.
  • Input field actions should be triggered by pressing enter on the keyboard or by clicking the send button. Ensure that the app sends the message content to the OpenAI API for processing.

2. Features

  • The app must send user messages to the OpenAI API, receive the generated text, and display it in the chat interface.
  • The application should generate diverse text outputs (stories, poetry, technical articles, dialogues of fictional characters, etc.) based on user inputs.
  • Users should be able to customize the text generation process, including adjusting the length of the output text, specifying the creative temperature, determining the use of specific keywords, and deciding the tone of the text (formal, informal, old-fashioned, modern, etc.).
  • The application should allow users to provide detailed prompts or context for the text generation, such as a starting line for a story, a specific question to answer, or a detailed scenario for generating a dialogue.
  • The application should provide an interactive mode where users can continuously provide new prompts based on the generated text, effectively creating a back-and-forth conversation with the AI.
  • The application must gracefully handle potential API errors.

Judging Criteria:

  • Functionality: How well does the application function? Does it generate text as per the given specifications and user prompts?
  • Creativity: Does the application include unique or innovative features that set it apart?
  • Design: Has the application been built in accordance with the provided design?
  • Code Quality: Is the code well-structured, well-commented, and easy to understand?
  • Documentation: Is the documentation clear, thorough, and informative, offering guidance to future developers or users?
  • Usage of OpenAI API: How effectively and efficiently does the application utilize the OpenAI API?

Review Scorecard:

  • Challenge Requirements: 50 Points
  • Does the submission meet all the specifications outlined in the challenge brief?
  • Best Practice & Technical Requirements: 30 Points
  • Does the submission adhere to best practices in code structuring, commenting, error handling, and UX/UI design?
  • Deployment Guide: 20 Points
  • Is there clear documentation on how to deploy and use the application?
  • Minimum Passing Score = 70
  • Challenge Scorecard: Make sure to keep these scorecard categories in mind as you work through the challenge to attain a high score!
  • https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/15E_jO3fHMqs5mEIx23qCdizekjajF7mtaloQ57flqbM/edit?usp=sharing

Remember, the journey is as important as the destination. Have fun and learn as - Good luck!

Challenge Deliverables
Submit a ZIP file containing the whole source code. Create proper documentation to help us set up your review.

Audience
Elastic Team Community Members

File Format
We would like your name ideas submitted by following these rules:

  • Use ZIP file format.
  • Filename Format: Elastic-Team-OpenAI-Smart-Text-Generator-Challenge-YourName.zip
  • You are only allowed to send 1 submission.

Prizes
The top 20 Elastic Team members will be awarded a £100 gift card (or similar, depending on your region.)

Timeline

  • This challenge will run for 2 weeks!
  • Start: 3:00 pm (London, GMT+1), June 23rd 2023
  • End: 3:00 pm (London, GMT+1), July 7th 2023
  • Late Submissions will be reviewed but are not eligible for prizes, so send them in sooner than later!
  • Review Timeline: July 7th 2023 to July 14th 2023

Questions and How to Submit

  • Ask challenge questions in Discord! We have a channel for discussing this challenge!
  • Please email your final ZIP file to adam.morehead@distributed.com before 3:00 pm (London, GMT+1), July 7th 2023
  • Use this subject when sending your email:  Elastic Team OpenAI - Smart Text Generator Challenge - Your Name

Winner Selection

  • The Distributed Community team will select and organize the top submission
  • We will survey the ET members for their favorite submission
  • The Community team will make all final decisions

The Fine Print

  • This challenge is only open to both Academy and Elastic Team members
  • Distributed will provide 20 Academy/Elastic Team members with a £100 gift card or equivalent, depending on your region of the world. (We will work with you on what works best!)
  • As an Elastic Team member, you are NOT required to join this challenge.
  • Make sure you have FUN with this challenge!

Challenge Author
Elastic Team Member: Dedy Wahyudi

Distributed Community Team
Diana, Adam, Dedy, Muhammad
